WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-US

00:00:00.180 --> 00:00:01.410
- It can be tough

00:00:01.410 --> 00:00:03.776
to identify as a Zionist these days.

00:00:10.050 --> 00:00:12.060
- But are you ready for a hot take?

00:00:12.060 --> 00:00:14.850
I'm willing to bet that some
of the folks on that subway

00:00:14.850 --> 00:00:17.280
were Zionists, even if
they didn't know it,

00:00:17.280 --> 00:00:19.860
because Zionism is simply the belief

00:00:19.860 --> 00:00:22.410
that Jews have a right
to govern themselves

00:00:22.410 --> 00:00:24.120
in their ancestral homeland.

00:00:24.120 --> 00:00:28.350
Anti-Zionism is the belief
that, well, we don't.

00:00:28.350 --> 00:00:31.200
Bad news for the
anti-Zionist crowd, though,

00:00:31.200 --> 00:00:34.080
the Zionist dream has already come true.

00:00:34.080 --> 00:00:37.590
We do have self-determination
in our ancestral homeland.

00:00:37.590 --> 00:00:40.590
It's called the modern state of Israel,

00:00:40.590 --> 00:00:44.350
so if we have our own country,
do we still need Zionism?

00:00:44.350 --> 00:00:47.350
(graphic crunching)

00:00:48.900 --> 00:00:52.140
You might have heard that
Judaism isn't Zionism.

00:00:52.140 --> 00:00:55.140
After all, you don't need to
be Jewish to be a Zionist.

00:00:55.140 --> 00:00:58.080
There are more Christian
Zionists in the United States

00:00:58.080 --> 00:01:00.720
than there are Jews in the entire world,

00:01:00.720 --> 00:01:03.000
but let me blow your mind for a second.

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:06.420
Judaism is inherently Zionist.

00:01:06.420 --> 00:01:08.730
I can already see you rolling your eyes.

00:01:08.730 --> 00:01:11.220
Zionism is a modern concept.

00:01:11.220 --> 00:01:15.360
The word Zionism wasn't
invented until 1890.

00:01:15.360 --> 00:01:17.610
That's technically true.

00:01:17.610 --> 00:01:20.580
Zionism, as a modern political movement,

00:01:20.580 --> 00:01:22.650
began in the late 1800s,

00:01:22.650 --> 00:01:26.010
but the Jewish connection
to the Land of Israel,

00:01:26.010 --> 00:01:28.440
that's 4,000 years old.

00:01:28.440 --> 00:01:32.490
The foundational text of our
religion is the Hebrew Bible.

00:01:32.490 --> 00:01:34.080
From the very first book,

00:01:34.080 --> 00:01:36.600
Israel is presented as the promised land

00:01:36.600 --> 00:01:38.610
and the rest is history.

00:01:38.610 --> 00:01:41.040
For centuries, we lived and ruled

00:01:41.040 --> 00:01:43.860
and squabbled with each
other in this land.

00:01:43.860 --> 00:01:46.980
Sometimes, our kings paid
tribute to foreign empires.

00:01:46.980 --> 00:01:49.680
Other times, we were fully independent,

00:01:49.680 --> 00:01:54.240
but no matter who was in
charge, one thing was constant:

00:01:54.240 --> 00:01:56.760
Our land was our home,

00:01:56.760 --> 00:01:59.670
and then the Babylonians came along.

00:01:59.670 --> 00:02:03.540
They destroyed our capital and
hauled us off to captivity,

00:02:03.540 --> 00:02:06.930
but instead of disappearing, we survived.

00:02:06.930 --> 00:02:08.760
Thousands of years later,

00:02:08.760 --> 00:02:10.950
we're still singing the songs we wrote

00:02:10.950 --> 00:02:12.930
in that long-ago exile,

00:02:12.930 --> 00:02:15.450
dreaming of our return to Zion,

00:02:15.450 --> 00:02:17.460
and that dream came true.

00:02:17.460 --> 00:02:21.420
We did return to Zion where
we reestablished our kingdom,

00:02:21.420 --> 00:02:24.660
but Jewish self-determination
in the Land of Israel

00:02:24.660 --> 00:02:25.830
came to an end

00:02:25.830 --> 00:02:29.250
when the Roman Empire
destroyed our communities,

00:02:29.250 --> 00:02:34.140
enslaved our people, and
sent us into exile once more.

00:02:34.140 --> 00:02:37.560
A handful of Jews remained
in the Land of Israel.

00:02:37.560 --> 00:02:39.420
The rest of us scattered,

00:02:39.420 --> 00:02:43.650
ending up anywhere from Iraq
to Poland to the Caribbean,

00:02:43.650 --> 00:02:46.410
but no matter where we were in the world,

00:02:46.410 --> 00:02:48.840
one thing remained constant:

00:02:48.840 --> 00:02:51.810
Three times a day, we
turn towards Jerusalem,

00:02:51.810 --> 00:02:54.630
and begged God to return us to Zion.

00:02:54.630 --> 00:02:56.190
We end each Passover seder

00:02:56.190 --> 00:02:59.040
with cries of, "Next year in Jerusalem."

00:02:59.040 --> 00:03:03.030
Every summer we observe the
solemn holiday of Tisha B'Av,

00:03:03.030 --> 00:03:05.940
which commemorates the
destruction of our home,

00:03:05.940 --> 00:03:08.640
and even in moments of
joy and celebration,

00:03:08.640 --> 00:03:12.150
we made a point of
remembering our greatest loss.

00:03:12.150 --> 00:03:13.890
Ever wonder why Jewish weddings

00:03:13.890 --> 00:03:16.050
end with the smashing of a glass?

00:03:16.050 --> 00:03:17.070
Now you know.

00:03:17.070 --> 00:03:19.920
It's a symbol of the
destruction of Jerusalem

00:03:19.920 --> 00:03:21.840
thousands of years ago.

00:03:21.840 --> 00:03:26.640
For 1,900 years, we prayed
and longed and remembered,

00:03:26.640 --> 00:03:27.810
and over the centuries,

00:03:27.810 --> 00:03:32.010
a slow trickle of Jewish
refugees, mystics, and pilgrims

00:03:32.010 --> 00:03:33.990
made their way back home,

00:03:33.990 --> 00:03:37.200
but as the 19th century
gave way to the 20th,

00:03:37.200 --> 00:03:39.870
that trickle became a flood.

00:03:39.870 --> 00:03:42.600
Nationalism was sweeping the globe.

00:03:42.600 --> 00:03:45.510
Ordinary people living under great empires

00:03:45.510 --> 00:03:47.520
dreamed of self-rule,

00:03:47.520 --> 00:03:51.300
and Jews who had survived
two millennia of persecution

00:03:51.300 --> 00:03:52.650
in foreign lands

00:03:52.650 --> 00:03:54.600
began to think of Jerusalem

00:03:54.600 --> 00:03:58.650
as more than just a metaphor
or distant religious concept.

00:03:58.650 --> 00:04:02.040
It was a real place,
only a boat ride away.

00:04:02.040 --> 00:04:03.930
Okay, but why now?

00:04:03.930 --> 00:04:06.000
The the Jews had 2,000 years

00:04:06.000 --> 00:04:08.490
to turn that trickle to a flood, right?

00:04:08.490 --> 00:04:10.980
See, the final years of the 19th century

00:04:10.980 --> 00:04:14.250
where a particularly bad
time for Jews in Europe.

00:04:14.250 --> 00:04:18.330
Across the Russian Empire,
violence and oppression soared.

00:04:18.330 --> 00:04:22.470
The Jews were tired of
pogroms and antisemitic laws,

00:04:22.470 --> 00:04:25.110
and though they couldn't know
what shape it would take,

00:04:25.110 --> 00:04:27.960
some predicted a catastrophe was coming.

00:04:27.960 --> 00:04:31.170
Even so-called enlightened
societies, like France,

00:04:31.170 --> 00:04:33.600
seemed unable to rid themselves

00:04:33.600 --> 00:04:36.150
of their ingrained hatred of Jews.

00:04:36.150 --> 00:04:39.750
In 1894, a decorated French Army officer

00:04:39.750 --> 00:04:41.370
named Alfred Dreyfus

00:04:41.370 --> 00:04:44.820
was framed for treason,
publicly humiliated,

00:04:44.820 --> 00:04:47.310
and deported to Devil's Island,

00:04:47.310 --> 00:04:49.620
but there was no evidence for the crime.

00:04:49.620 --> 00:04:52.770
In fact, it turned out that
the French Army's high command

00:04:52.770 --> 00:04:54.600
had known he was innocent,

00:04:54.600 --> 00:04:57.750
but the mistake was embarrassing for them,

00:04:57.750 --> 00:04:59.790
so they left him in prison.

00:04:59.790 --> 00:05:01.170
They believed that no one

00:05:01.170 --> 00:05:03.090
would look too closely at this case.

00:05:03.090 --> 00:05:05.730
After all, Dreyfus was a Jew.

00:05:05.730 --> 00:05:08.370
The generals had good
reason to think that way.

00:05:08.370 --> 00:05:10.410
The country that had once championed

00:05:10.410 --> 00:05:14.400
liberté, égalité, et fraternité

00:05:14.400 --> 00:05:17.910
was convulsing with antisemitic riots,

00:05:17.910 --> 00:05:20.940
but some people were looking closely,

00:05:20.940 --> 00:05:22.950
including a Viennese journalist

00:05:22.950 --> 00:05:25.800
who had been sent to
France to cover the riots.

00:05:25.800 --> 00:05:29.370
What he saw made him
realize that antisemitism

00:05:29.370 --> 00:05:32.310
was a disease that couldn't be cured.

00:05:32.310 --> 00:05:35.610
That journalist's name was Theodor Herzl.

00:05:35.610 --> 00:05:38.820
Like Dreyfus, Herzl
was an assimilated Jew.

00:05:38.820 --> 00:05:40.740
He'd done his best to blend in,

00:05:40.740 --> 00:05:43.710
to embrace every part
of society open to him,

00:05:43.710 --> 00:05:47.700
but now he found himself
gripped by despair.

00:05:47.700 --> 00:05:50.250
What hope did the Jewish People have

00:05:50.250 --> 00:05:53.610
if even the most
assimilated high-ranking Jew

00:05:53.610 --> 00:05:57.450
could be brought so low
on so little evidence?

00:05:57.450 --> 00:06:00.270
Pogroms were driving Jews
out of Eastern Europe

00:06:00.270 --> 00:06:01.440
in the millions.

00:06:01.440 --> 00:06:05.370
Antisemitism had infected
the highest levels of society

00:06:05.370 --> 00:06:08.040
in the supposedly enlightened West.

00:06:08.040 --> 00:06:10.890
What kind of future did that
leave for Europe's Jews?

00:06:10.890 --> 00:06:13.230
I sat down with Haviv Rettig Gur,

00:06:13.230 --> 00:06:15.210
a senior analyst for
"The Times of Israel,"

00:06:15.210 --> 00:06:17.910
to talk through some of his ideas.

00:06:17.910 --> 00:06:21.540
- The Zionist predictive
power is astonishing.

00:06:21.540 --> 00:06:25.263
When Zionism forms its institutions
and gives its warnings,

00:06:26.370 --> 00:06:29.550
Herzl writes about a
catastrophe that's coming

00:06:29.550 --> 00:06:31.020
and says, "They're gonna come for us."

00:06:31.020 --> 00:06:33.030
He literally uses those words,

00:06:33.030 --> 00:06:35.760
and he's talking about mass
killings, among other things,

00:06:35.760 --> 00:06:39.330
and expulsions and
theft and expropriation.

00:06:39.330 --> 00:06:41.370
They talk, 50 years ahead of time,

00:06:41.370 --> 00:06:42.930
about what's going to happen,

00:06:42.930 --> 00:06:45.540
and all of it plays out
just like they predicted

00:06:45.540 --> 00:06:47.832
because it was rooted
in a real understanding

00:06:47.832 --> 00:06:50.130
of the sociology of the time.

00:06:50.130 --> 00:06:52.110
- Herzl decided there was no point

00:06:52.110 --> 00:06:54.150
in fighting antisemitism.

00:06:54.150 --> 00:06:57.390
If the Jews wanted a
life free of persecution,

00:06:57.390 --> 00:06:59.190
they'd have to build it elsewhere,

00:06:59.190 --> 00:07:01.770
away from people who hated them.

00:07:01.770 --> 00:07:03.360
- Zionism comes in and says

00:07:03.360 --> 00:07:07.290
the danger is not old antisem-,
religious antisemitism.

00:07:07.290 --> 00:07:09.180
The danger's so much bigger,

00:07:09.180 --> 00:07:11.940
and if we don't get out,
we face a catastrophe.

00:07:11.940 --> 00:07:15.120
- Like other nations,
they'd need their own state.

00:07:15.120 --> 00:07:17.670
They would need to become Zionists:

00:07:17.670 --> 00:07:18.570
People who believe

00:07:18.570 --> 00:07:21.720
that the Jewish People had a
right to self-determination

00:07:21.720 --> 00:07:23.670
in their ancestral homeland.

00:07:23.670 --> 00:07:26.700
Though, of course, it
wasn't quite that easy.

00:07:26.700 --> 00:07:29.640
It wouldn't be a Jewish
story without an argument,

00:07:29.640 --> 00:07:32.880
and these early Zionists loved to argue.

00:07:32.880 --> 00:07:35.160
Sure, they agreed on the basic premise,

00:07:35.160 --> 00:07:37.740
but what would
self-determination look like?

00:07:37.740 --> 00:07:40.050
What should their homeland be?

00:07:40.050 --> 00:07:43.110
There were as many answers
as there were Zionists,

00:07:43.110 --> 00:07:47.220
but six common themes emerged
in these endless debates,

00:07:47.220 --> 00:07:50.910
six types of Zionism,
which sometimes overlapped

00:07:50.910 --> 00:07:53.490
and sometimes contradicted each other.

00:07:53.490 --> 00:07:56.940
Six Zionisms, which still exist today.

00:07:56.940 --> 00:08:00.480
For Political Zionists,
the answer was simple.

00:08:00.480 --> 00:08:03.780
The Jewish state should
look like all other states.

00:08:03.780 --> 00:08:06.120
It was the Jewish People's lack of a state

00:08:06.120 --> 00:08:08.880
that was at the root of all antisemitism.

00:08:08.880 --> 00:08:10.560
Once they had a state,

00:08:10.560 --> 00:08:13.230
poof, they'd be just like everyone else,

00:08:13.230 --> 00:08:15.380
and antisemitism would disappear.

00:08:15.380 --> 00:08:17.460
- (groans) Wouldn't that be nice.

00:08:17.460 --> 00:08:18.960
- For Labor Zionists,

00:08:18.960 --> 00:08:21.540
the Jewish state would be
better than all others.

00:08:21.540 --> 00:08:23.850
Its economy would focus on agriculture

00:08:23.850 --> 00:08:25.860
in a nod to the Jewish People's roots

00:08:25.860 --> 00:08:28.290
as simple farmers in their homeland.

00:08:28.290 --> 00:08:31.560
This time, though, they'd
ditch the religious monarchy

00:08:31.560 --> 00:08:35.520
in favor of a fully secular
socialist government

00:08:35.520 --> 00:08:38.280
for the people by the people.

00:08:38.280 --> 00:08:40.560
Cultural Zionists, on the other hand,

00:08:40.560 --> 00:08:43.710
dreamed of building a
cultural and spiritual hub

00:08:43.710 --> 00:08:45.078
for Jewish peoplehood

00:08:45.078 --> 00:08:47.760
where the Jewish soul would flourish.

00:08:47.760 --> 00:08:51.300
The Jews would read and
write and sing in Hebrew.

00:08:51.300 --> 00:08:53.370
They'd create art with Jewish themes,

00:08:53.370 --> 00:08:55.950
hold conversations about Jewish topics,

00:08:55.950 --> 00:08:58.200
and regenerate Jewish culture.

00:08:58.200 --> 00:09:00.570
They didn't even need
to govern themselves.

00:09:00.570 --> 00:09:03.870
They just wanted a Jewish
cultural renaissance

00:09:03.870 --> 00:09:06.930
in the place where the
Jewish People were born.

00:09:06.930 --> 00:09:09.060
Meanwhile, Revisionist Zionists

00:09:09.060 --> 00:09:12.120
dreamed of a big, bold Jewish state

00:09:12.120 --> 00:09:14.970
within the borders of biblical Israel.

00:09:14.970 --> 00:09:17.970
Revisionist Zionists weren't
necessarily religious,

00:09:17.970 --> 00:09:21.660
but they were extremely proud
of their Jewish identity.

00:09:21.660 --> 00:09:23.970
They idolized the Jewish warriors

00:09:23.970 --> 00:09:25.650
of the Bible and of history.

00:09:25.650 --> 00:09:27.547
- When the other Zionist
factions are saying,

00:09:27.547 --> 00:09:28.777
"Maybe it can be an autonomy.

00:09:28.777 --> 00:09:31.620
"Maybe it can be something
linked to some larger state,"

00:09:31.620 --> 00:09:32.497
the revisionists say, "Guys,

00:09:32.497 --> 00:09:33.517
"the only way we survive this thing

00:09:33.517 --> 00:09:35.827
"is if we have complete
self-determination and self-reliance

00:09:35.827 --> 00:09:38.197
"and our own army and our own
borders and our own state.

00:09:38.197 --> 00:09:40.947
"Otherwise, it's not gonna work."

00:09:52.620 --> 00:09:54.930
- They knew there was a fight ahead,

00:09:54.930 --> 00:09:56.670
and they were prepared for it.

00:09:56.670 --> 00:09:58.020
Religious Zionists believed

00:09:58.020 --> 00:09:59.910
the revival of the Jewish homeland

00:09:59.910 --> 00:10:01.830
was a religious obligation.

00:10:01.830 --> 00:10:04.440
Their Zionism was the closest in nature

00:10:04.440 --> 00:10:06.990
to the Zionism that
Jews had been espousing

00:10:06.990 --> 00:10:08.580
for thousands of years.

00:10:08.580 --> 00:10:11.400
They believed that the
Jewish return to Zion

00:10:11.400 --> 00:10:14.130
was a sign that Judaism's
promised redemption

00:10:14.130 --> 00:10:15.780
was close at hand.

00:10:15.780 --> 00:10:18.090
God was sending them a message,

00:10:18.090 --> 00:10:19.590
they just had to listen.

00:10:19.590 --> 00:10:22.470
And because every thesis
has an antithesis,

00:10:22.470 --> 00:10:26.070
the religious Zionists
had a diametric opposite.

00:10:26.070 --> 00:10:28.170
These were equally religious Jews

00:10:28.170 --> 00:10:31.470
who studied the same texts
and said the same prayers

00:10:31.470 --> 00:10:33.510
who were also waiting for the Messiah

00:10:33.510 --> 00:10:35.430
and the ultimate redemption.

00:10:35.430 --> 00:10:39.570
They just disagreed completely
on who would make it happen.

00:10:39.570 --> 00:10:42.120
These were the religious non-Zionists

00:10:42.120 --> 00:10:44.940
who believed that Jews had no business

00:10:44.940 --> 00:10:48.270
trying to establish a secular
state in the Holy Land.

00:10:48.270 --> 00:10:50.070
Only God could decide

00:10:50.070 --> 00:10:53.070
when it was time for his
children to return home,

00:10:53.070 --> 00:10:55.890
and they believed that
God wasn't too happy

00:10:55.890 --> 00:10:59.040
about his children
building a secular state

00:10:59.040 --> 00:11:03.420
with public transit on
Shabbat and girls in shorts.

00:11:03.420 --> 00:11:06.990
Now, before we go any
further, I wanna be clear.

00:11:06.990 --> 00:11:10.380
Jews who object to Zionism
on religious grounds

00:11:10.380 --> 00:11:13.200
also long for a return to Zion

00:11:13.200 --> 00:11:15.540
for the rebuilding of the holy Temple,

00:11:15.540 --> 00:11:18.300
for the establishment
of a religious monarchy

00:11:18.300 --> 00:11:19.410
in the Holy Land.

00:11:19.410 --> 00:11:22.740
They also end their seders
with, "Next year in Jerusalem,"

00:11:22.740 --> 00:11:25.680
and their weddings with
the smashing of a glass.

00:11:25.680 --> 00:11:29.190
Even they believe that
Israel is the Jewish homeland

00:11:29.190 --> 00:11:31.140
promised to us by God.

00:11:31.140 --> 00:11:33.420
There were other types of Zionism too.

00:11:33.420 --> 00:11:36.060
The movement was as messy and complicated

00:11:36.060 --> 00:11:38.640
and multidimensional as Jews themselves.

00:11:38.640 --> 00:11:41.670
It was everything everywhere all at once,

00:11:41.670 --> 00:11:44.970
but as all these figures
bickered and negotiated

00:11:44.970 --> 00:11:47.940
and did their best to
build their own utopias,

00:11:47.940 --> 00:11:50.010
shadows were gathering.

00:11:50.010 --> 00:11:52.350
Antisemitic laws were common in Europe,

00:11:52.350 --> 00:11:54.450
but when the Nazis came to power,

00:11:54.450 --> 00:11:57.180
those laws became more and more severe,

00:11:57.180 --> 00:12:00.720
and as country after country
fell to the Nazi assault,

00:12:00.720 --> 00:12:04.710
they too began instituting
strict anti-Jewish laws.

00:12:04.710 --> 00:12:07.410
Jews were no longer
allowed to go to school

00:12:07.410 --> 00:12:09.810
or to work or to public parks.

00:12:09.810 --> 00:12:12.210
Ordinary people stood by and watched

00:12:12.210 --> 00:12:16.950
as Jewish shops and synagogues
were smashed and burned,

00:12:16.950 --> 00:12:19.050
as Jews were beaten in the street,

00:12:19.050 --> 00:12:21.120
as they were crowded into ghettos,

00:12:21.120 --> 00:12:23.850
as they were deported to the East.

00:12:23.850 --> 00:12:26.970
The lucky ones got out
as soon as they could,

00:12:26.970 --> 00:12:28.920
but most weren't lucky.

00:12:28.920 --> 00:12:32.520
By 1946, a third of the
world's Jews were gone,

00:12:32.520 --> 00:12:35.100
and all those ideological Zionisms,

00:12:35.100 --> 00:12:38.100
the competing visions of
the perfect Jewish state,

00:12:38.100 --> 00:12:39.360
they were gone too,

00:12:39.360 --> 00:12:41.400
or at least they were secondary now

00:12:41.400 --> 00:12:43.890
to the only Zionism that really mattered,

00:12:43.890 --> 00:12:45.090
the one that would save

00:12:45.090 --> 00:12:48.390
the world's remaining
Jews from annihilation.

00:12:48.390 --> 00:12:51.390
First, they'd focus on surviving.

00:12:51.390 --> 00:12:53.700
Then they could argue about the specifics

00:12:53.700 --> 00:12:54.660
because it wouldn't matter

00:12:54.660 --> 00:12:57.360
if the new state was secular or religious,

00:12:57.360 --> 00:13:00.240
if its language was Hebrew
or Yiddish or Ladino.

00:13:00.240 --> 00:13:01.350
It wouldn't matter

00:13:01.350 --> 00:13:04.110
if there were no more
Jews left to live in it.

00:13:04.110 --> 00:13:07.560
They argued, and they
negotiated, and they compromised,

00:13:07.560 --> 00:13:09.900
but in the end, they just did it.

00:13:09.900 --> 00:13:12.420
The Labor Zionists and the Revisionists,

00:13:12.420 --> 00:13:14.670
the Cultural Zionists and the Religious

00:13:14.670 --> 00:13:18.240
did everything they could
to build a Jewish state,

00:13:18.240 --> 00:13:20.460
and though the non-Zionists
were frustrated

00:13:20.460 --> 00:13:22.440
and opposed to the whole project,

00:13:22.440 --> 00:13:24.870
they understood that this was happening.

00:13:24.870 --> 00:13:26.820
It was useless to interfere,

00:13:26.820 --> 00:13:30.180
and more than 70 years later, here we are.

00:13:30.180 --> 00:13:31.140
This isn't the state

00:13:31.140 --> 00:13:33.570
that any of the early Zionists envisioned,

00:13:33.570 --> 00:13:35.670
but I think every Zionist leader

00:13:35.670 --> 00:13:38.100
would recognize elements of their vision

00:13:38.100 --> 00:13:42.000
in this messy, multicultural,
miraculous state

00:13:42.000 --> 00:13:43.410
that exists today.

00:13:43.410 --> 00:13:45.630
Herzl understood how dangerous

00:13:45.630 --> 00:13:47.550
antisemitism would be for Jews,

00:13:47.550 --> 00:13:51.120
but even he, that prophet of catastrophe,

00:13:51.120 --> 00:13:54.420
was too optimistic about Zionism's powers.

00:13:54.420 --> 00:13:57.536
- What was the lived experience
of millions of people

00:13:57.536 --> 00:14:00.840
who became Zionists in the 20th century?

00:14:00.840 --> 00:14:03.720
It was essentially the emptying
out of entire continents.

00:14:03.720 --> 00:14:05.610
They couldn't live anywhere else.

00:14:05.610 --> 00:14:06.540
If you're an Israeli Jew

00:14:06.540 --> 00:14:08.250
and you look out at
the Eastern Hemisphere,

00:14:08.250 --> 00:14:09.810
all the other Jews are dead.

00:14:09.810 --> 00:14:11.730
Your grandparents are refugees.

00:14:11.730 --> 00:14:14.130
No other option for
survival was open to them.

00:14:14.130 --> 00:14:15.783
America's doors closed in 1921.

00:14:16.620 --> 00:14:19.020
All the rest of the Jews
of the world become Israeli

00:14:19.020 --> 00:14:22.560
or the Jews of Europe and the
Arab world become Israeli.

00:14:22.560 --> 00:14:25.860
- Antisemitism wasn't rooted
in our lack of a state.

00:14:25.860 --> 00:14:29.640
In fact, our state has
become a convenient target

00:14:29.640 --> 00:14:32.070
for those same old Jew-haters,

00:14:32.070 --> 00:14:34.080
even providing cover for those

00:14:34.080 --> 00:14:38.460
who claim they are merely
anti-Zionists, not antisemites.

00:14:38.460 --> 00:14:40.470
- I want Israel to be dismantled.

00:14:40.470 --> 00:14:41.543
- It is right to rebel.

00:14:42.522 --> 00:14:44.400
Israel, go to hell.

00:14:44.400 --> 00:14:45.780
- Anti-Zionism is the argument

00:14:45.780 --> 00:14:48.570
that they shouldn't have
survived the 20th century.

00:14:48.570 --> 00:14:50.010
That sure feels antisemitic

00:14:50.010 --> 00:14:52.680
to the Jew who you're saying it to.

00:14:52.680 --> 00:14:55.530
Anti-Zionism need not be antisemitism

00:14:55.530 --> 00:14:58.500
unless it's willfully ignorant on purpose

00:14:58.500 --> 00:15:00.090
because it is virtue signaling

00:15:00.090 --> 00:15:03.510
about the very survival of
an entire human community.

00:15:03.510 --> 00:15:07.950
- In Europe, rioters had
screamed, "Go to Palestine,"

00:15:07.950 --> 00:15:11.340
often with an anti-Jewish slur
added in for good measure.

00:15:11.340 --> 00:15:13.350
In Israel, we watched reports

00:15:13.350 --> 00:15:16.723
of protestors demanding
we go back to Europe.

00:15:16.723 --> 00:15:17.610
- Go back to Europe,

00:15:17.610 --> 00:15:19.198
where you're originally from.

00:15:19.198 --> 00:15:21.690
- They killed us there too.

00:15:21.690 --> 00:15:23.850
- Go back to the mass grave

00:15:23.850 --> 00:15:26.970
that swallowed one third of your people,

00:15:26.970 --> 00:15:29.670
but Herzl was also right.

00:15:29.670 --> 00:15:33.570
He envisioned a place where
we determine our own destiny,

00:15:33.570 --> 00:15:35.670
and that's exactly what we're doing.

00:15:35.670 --> 00:15:36.780
He dreamed of a place

00:15:36.780 --> 00:15:39.780
where children would grow
up Jewish and unafraid,

00:15:39.780 --> 00:15:43.530
a country that would
absorb 800,000 refugees

00:15:43.530 --> 00:15:44.700
from the Muslim world

00:15:44.700 --> 00:15:48.540
and 1 million from the former
USSR, no matter the cost,

00:15:48.540 --> 00:15:52.620
just because they were Jews
who needed a place to go.

00:15:52.620 --> 00:15:54.750
Cultural Zionists won too.

00:15:54.750 --> 00:15:57.540
Half the world's Jews use
the language of the Bible

00:15:57.540 --> 00:16:00.390
to order lattes and comment on TikTok

00:16:00.390 --> 00:16:02.940
and get into arguments with traffic cops.

00:16:02.940 --> 00:16:06.570
Our music combines East and
West, ancient and modern,

00:16:06.570 --> 00:16:08.160
biblical and secular.

00:16:08.160 --> 00:16:12.330
Our comedians parody prime
ministers and biblical kings.

00:16:12.330 --> 00:16:13.590
Revisionist Zionists

00:16:13.590 --> 00:16:16.410
created a language of pride and confidence

00:16:16.410 --> 00:16:19.650
that was meaningful to
so many in the new state.

00:16:19.650 --> 00:16:21.120
They had predicted correctly

00:16:21.120 --> 00:16:24.210
the Jews in Israel would
live on their swords.

00:16:24.210 --> 00:16:28.230
As I'm recording this, the
IDF is fighting Hamas in Gaza

00:16:28.230 --> 00:16:30.720
and striking Hezbollah targets in Lebanon,

00:16:30.720 --> 00:16:33.600
and even though saying "I told you so"

00:16:33.600 --> 00:16:36.750
is one of life's greatest
and pettiest pleasures,

00:16:36.750 --> 00:16:39.210
I don't think early
Revisionists would be happy

00:16:39.210 --> 00:16:41.310
that they were right on this point.

00:16:41.310 --> 00:16:43.200
As for the Religious Zionists,

00:16:43.200 --> 00:16:46.290
well, the devout see
God's hand everywhere.

00:16:46.290 --> 00:16:47.940
It's this faith that allows them

00:16:47.940 --> 00:16:50.970
to continue living full and joyous lives

00:16:50.970 --> 00:16:53.670
in a state that demands so much.

00:16:53.670 --> 00:16:57.690
The only party that truly
lost were the non-Zionists.

00:16:57.690 --> 00:17:00.960
Some accepted that loss
and tried to move forward.

00:17:00.960 --> 00:17:04.890
Ironically, a small but
significant percentage of Israelis

00:17:04.890 --> 00:17:07.290
are non-Zionists.

00:17:07.290 --> 00:17:10.530
Even more ironically, they
enjoy full citizenship

00:17:10.530 --> 00:17:12.840
and representation in
the Israeli government

00:17:12.840 --> 00:17:14.580
where they've carved out a niche

00:17:14.580 --> 00:17:17.010
advocating for their religious interests.

00:17:17.010 --> 00:17:18.990
As for the anti-Zionist protestors

00:17:18.990 --> 00:17:21.960
who believe the state of
Israel should not exist,

00:17:21.960 --> 00:17:26.010
well, I'd encourage them to
step into the 21st century

00:17:26.010 --> 00:17:28.920
where we have SodaStream and camera pills

00:17:28.920 --> 00:17:32.580
and the microprocessors
that are in every single PC,

00:17:32.580 --> 00:17:35.190
and also, to step backwards

00:17:35.190 --> 00:17:37.710
to the 19th and early 20th centuries

00:17:37.710 --> 00:17:40.440
to the time of violence and pogroms

00:17:40.440 --> 00:17:42.660
and strict immigration quotas,

00:17:42.660 --> 00:17:45.510
and I'd like to see them try and explain

00:17:45.510 --> 00:17:48.300
to those fleeing desperate Jews

00:17:48.300 --> 00:17:50.490
where else they should have gone.

00:17:50.490 --> 00:17:53.227
- The only thing a Zionist
has to say to them is,

00:17:53.227 --> 00:17:54.907
"It must be really nice

00:17:54.907 --> 00:17:58.987
"to live in a safe, Western place

00:17:58.987 --> 00:18:01.477
"where you can meditate on such things,

00:18:01.477 --> 00:18:04.327
"and my job is to make sure my kids live.

00:18:04.327 --> 00:18:06.967
"Your job is to decide
whether it's moral or not

00:18:06.967 --> 00:18:08.670
"for my kids to have survived."

00:18:08.670 --> 00:18:11.280
- So do we need Zionism?

00:18:11.280 --> 00:18:14.100
Well, it's a complicated question.

00:18:14.100 --> 00:18:17.400
The state's founders had
big, conflicting dreams

00:18:17.400 --> 00:18:20.610
about what a Zionist
utopia should look like.

00:18:20.610 --> 00:18:23.580
All came true in some ways.

00:18:23.580 --> 00:18:25.950
None were fully realized.

00:18:25.950 --> 00:18:28.380
We still have competing
visions for the future.

00:18:28.380 --> 00:18:31.950
We still argue and protest our government

00:18:31.950 --> 00:18:34.050
and write scathing op-eds,

00:18:34.050 --> 00:18:37.230
and we come together when it counts.

00:18:37.230 --> 00:18:39.630
We offer Jews around the globe

00:18:39.630 --> 00:18:43.140
the promise that our
ancestors were denied:

00:18:43.140 --> 00:18:47.010
You will always have a
home, and that's the point.

00:18:47.010 --> 00:18:50.760
That's the bedrock Zionism that
unites all of the Zionisms,

00:18:50.760 --> 00:18:54.840
from religious to secular,
from socialist to revisionist.

00:18:54.840 --> 00:18:56.640
We have a home.

00:18:56.640 --> 00:19:00.120
We will not be homeless
and vulnerable again.

00:19:00.120 --> 00:19:01.230
It's a messy home.

00:19:01.230 --> 00:19:03.000
We're still in the process of building it,

00:19:03.000 --> 00:19:06.990
of creating the kind of place
we want and deserve to live.

00:19:06.990 --> 00:19:10.170
That is what I mean when
I say that I'm a Zionist

00:19:10.170 --> 00:19:12.330
because I'm one of the millions of people

00:19:12.330 --> 00:19:13.920
doing the never-ending work

00:19:13.920 --> 00:19:18.410
of building a country worthy
of 2,000 years of longing.

